# Button — React

Package: `@acko/button`
Directive: `"use client"` (interactive)

## Architecture

The React component contains **zero Tailwind utilities**. All visual styling is in `@acko/css/button.css`. The component only composes CSS class names via `clsx`.

## Props Interface

```typescript
interface ButtonProps extends Omit<React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>, 'type'> {
  variant: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'inverted' | 'ghost' | 'link' | 'danger';
  size?: 'xs' | 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg' | 'xl';           // default: 'md'
  disabled?: boolean;
  loading?: boolean;
  iconLeft?: ReactNode;
  iconRight?: ReactNode;
  iconOnly?: boolean;
  fullWidth?: boolean;
  type?: 'button' | 'submit' | 'reset';                // default: 'button'
  children: ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}
```

## Component Pattern

```tsx
export const Button = forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ variant, size = 'md', disabled, loading, iconLeft, iconRight,
     iconOnly, fullWidth, type = 'button', className, children, ...rest }, ref) => {

    const isDisabled = disabled || loading;

    return (
      <button
        ref={ref}
        type={type}
        disabled={isDisabled}
        aria-busy={loading || undefined}
        aria-disabled={isDisabled || undefined}
        className={clsx(
          'acko-btn',
          `acko-btn-${variant}`,
          `acko-btn-${size}`,
          iconOnly && 'acko-btn-icon-only',
          loading && 'acko-btn-loading',
          isDisabled && 'acko-btn-disabled',
          fullWidth && 'acko-btn-full-width',
          className,
        )}
        {...rest}
      >
        {iconLeft && <span className="acko-btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">{iconLeft}</span>}
        {children}
        {iconRight && <span className="acko-btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">{iconRight}</span>}
        {loading && (
          <>
            <span className="acko-btn-spinner" aria-hidden="true" />
            <span className="sr-only">Loading, please wait</span>
          </>
        )}
      </button>
    );
  }
);

Button.displayName = 'Button';
```

**Key difference from old pattern:** No Tailwind utility classes in `className`. Everything — layout (`inline-flex items-center justify-center`), spacing (`gap: var(--scale-8)`), typography (`font-medium`), radius (`rounded-full`), cursor, select, position — is in the CSS file via `@apply` and explicit token properties.

## Hooks

None. Button is stateless — all behavior is props-driven.

## State Management

Stateless. `disabled` and `loading` come from props. No internal state.

## Event Handling

- `onClick` passed via `...rest` spread
- When `loading={true}`: component sets `disabled` on the native element + CSS `pointer-events: none`

## Text Formatting

Sentence case for all button labels. See `foundation/typography.mdc` → **Text Casing** for the full rule, exceptions (ACKO, IDV, NCB, proper nouns, etc.), and examples.

## Accessibility

| Attribute | When | Value |
|-----------|------|-------|
| `aria-busy` | `loading` | `true` |
| `aria-disabled` | `disabled \|\| loading` | `true` |
| `aria-hidden` | On icon spans, spinner | `true` |
| `role` | — | Native `<button>` semantics |
| Screen reader | `loading` | `<span className="sr-only">Loading, please wait</span>` |

Focus ring: handled in CSS via `:focus-visible` → `--shadow-focus-ring`.

## Keyboard

Native `<button>` keyboard behavior — Enter and Space trigger click. No custom keyboard handling needed.

## Dependencies

| Package | Type | Reason |
|---------|------|--------|
| `clsx` | dependency | Class composition |
| `react` | peer | React 18+ |
| `lucide-react` | peer (optional) | Only if icons are passed by consumer |

## Responsive Behavior

- Below 640px: consumers should apply `fullWidth` prop for primary/secondary CTAs
- Touch targets: minimum 44px height — xs (32px) should only be used for compact desktop UIs

## Exports

```typescript
